ABUJA – The Presidential Election Petition Tribunal sitting in Abuja has finally dismissed the petition filed by Alhaji Atiku Abubakar, presidential candidate of the main opposition Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) challenging the election of President Muhammadu Buhari of the All Peoples Congress (APC) in the February 23 presidential election. The lead judgement was read by Justice Mohammed Lawal Garba. …Details later